## Summary

### 1. **requirements.md** — Comprehensive Requirements Document

This document includes:

- **15 User Stories** (US-001 through US-015) covering:
  - User Registration & Login (High, 5 pts each)
  - Token Refresh (High, 3 pts)
  - Centralized Exception Handling (High, 5 pts)
  - Centralized Logging (High, 5 pts)
  - Circuit Breaker (Medium, 8 pts)
  - Swagger Documentation (High, 3 pts)
  - Health Checks (High, 2 pts)
  - User Profile & Deactivation (Medium, 5 & 3 pts)
  - Input Validation, RBAC, JWT, Database, Configuration

- **Every user story includes:**
  - Priority (High/Medium)
  - Story Points (Fibonacci: 1-13)
  - Testable Acceptance Criteria (e.g., AC-001.1, AC-001.2, etc.)
  - Error Scenarios with HTTP status codes (e.g., E-001.1, E-001.2)

- **13 Business Rules** (BR-001 through BR-013) covering:
  - Email uniqueness, password strength, role defaults
  - Soft deletes, audit trails, stateless authentication
  - Correlation ID uniqueness, sensitive data protection

- **Non-Functional Requirements** across 6 categories:
  - **Performance:** < 200ms response time (95th percentile)
  - **Security:** JWT auth, BCrypt passwords, RBAC, input validation, XSS/SQL injection prevention
  - **Reliability:** Health checks, graceful error handling, connection pooling, circuit breaker
  - **Observability:** Structured JSON logging with correlation IDs, request logging, audit trail
  - **Scalability:** Stateless architecture, horizontal scaling support
  - **Configuration:** Environment variables, dev/prod profiles, no hardcoded secrets

- **Domain Model** — User entity with:
  - 8 attributes with data types and constraints
  - Indexed fields (email, role, active) for performance
  - Soft delete support (active flag)

- **Traceability Matrix** — Maps all requirements to features with priority and story points

- **12 Open Questions** — Clarifications needed on database choice, refresh token strategy, rate limiting, 2FA, etc.

